Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @Potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 2cm slices, 
then chop into 2cm wide chips (no need to peel). Pop the chips onto a large 
#baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} then toss 
to coat. Spread out in a single layer. 

> Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{30-35%minutes}. 
Turn halfway through.

Put the @BBQ Sauce{32%g} into a large #bowl{}. Add the @Panko Breadcrumbs{25%g} and 
@Water{3%tbsp}. Season with the @salt{¼%tsp} for the burgers and @pepper{}, then 
add the @British Beef Mince{360%g}. Mix with your hands until well combined. Roll 
the mince into even-sized balls, then shape into 2cm thick burgers (1 per person).

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. TIP: The 
> burgers will shrink a little during cooking.

Pop the burgers onto a lightly oiled #baking tray{} and bake on the middle shelf 
of your oven until cooked through, ~{18-20%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{90%g}. When the burgers have ~{4%minutes} 
left, carefully place the cheese on top of the burgers and return to the oven 
to melt, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Whilst the burgers are cooking, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on 
medium-high heat. Lay in the @British Streaky Bacon{4%rasher} and fry until 
crispy and brown, ~{3-4%minutes} each side. Add the @Honey{15%g} and turn to coat. 

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min. 
> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon 
> thoroughly.

Remove the pan from the heat, set aside.

Meanwhile, trim the @Cucumber{½}(trimmed), then quarter lengthways. Chop widthways 
into small pieces. Roughly chop the @Dill{½} (stalks and all). Pop the cucumber, 
dill, @Balsamic Vinegar{12%ml} and @Wholegrain Mustard{17%g} into a bowl. Season 
with @salt{pinch}, @pepper{pinch} and @Sugar{1%tsp}. Mix until combined, then set aside.

A few mins before the chips are done, halve the @Glazed Burger Bun{2} and pop 
into the oven to warm, ~{2-3%minutes}.

When everything is ready, divide the burger buns between your #plates{}. Lay a 
cheesy burger patty onto the bun base. Top with the honey bacon rashers. Spread 
half the @Mayonnaise{64%g} onto the bun tops and sandwich together. Serve with 
the chips, pickled dill cucumber salad and the rest of your mayo for dipping 
alongside. Enjoy!